*'''Attack him/her''' : The dog/cat can attack (employee name) voluntary or after reveived a discipline. If the employee dies, you will be euthanazied.
*'''Bark''' : The dog/cat can bark at (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this.
*'''Beg''' : The dog/cat can beg for food at (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this unless they have high relationship.
*'''Hump'''
*'''Jump''' : The dog/cat can jump into (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back.
*'''Lick''' : The dog/cat can lick with (employee name). However, low/empty relationships employees will push you away.
*'''Lunge''' : The dog/cat can lunge to (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this.
*'''Mess''' : The dog/cat can mess with (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this.
*'''Nuzzle''' : The dog/cat can nuzzle with (employee name), doing this will result a reward, but doing this with employees with lowest relationship will push you away.
*'''Seek Attention'''
*'''Snarl''' : The dog/cat can snarl at (employee name), doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this.
*'''Sniff''' : The dog/cat can sniff (employee name) butt and get to know their scent, doing this will result (employee name) will argue back with the dog/cat for doing this.
*'''Spend time''' : The dog/cat can nuzzle with (employee name), doing this with employees with lowest relationship will result a argue back for doing this. The last option is considered like an animal abuse and not a misbehavior.
*'''Spray''' : The dog/cat can spray at (employee name), doing this will result a argue back for doing this.

